  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/252212066" />
    <a title="Diane Estrella" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5090505-diane-estrella"><img alt="Diane Estrella" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1582848730p2/5090505.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/252212066?book_show_action=true">Dec 28, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diane Estrella" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diane Estrella" href="/user/show/5090505-diane-estrella">Diane Estrella</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer252212066" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18416085402278314676">Do. Not. Steal.<br/><br/>Simple enough and pretty straight forward. I think most people would agree that this is a worthy law regardless of age, race, religion, or otherwise.<br/><br/>I love what Marja does in this book by not harping on the “do not” part, but on the what CAN we do part. The opposite of stealing is GIVING! Just not stealing, is fulfilling the law, but taking it the next step further and then going about our lives giving, IS the fulfillment of God’s grace.<br/><br/>Marja is a gifted teacher and does a wonderf</span>
  <span id="freeText18416085402278314676" style="display:none">Do. Not. Steal.<br /><br />Simple enough and pretty straight forward. I think most people would agree that this is a worthy law regardless of age, race, religion, or otherwise.<br /><br />I love what Marja does in this book by not harping on the “do not” part, but on the what CAN we do part. The opposite of stealing is GIVING! Just not stealing, is fulfilling the law, but taking it the next step further and then going about our lives giving, IS the fulfillment of God’s grace.<br /><br />Marja is a gifted teacher and does a wonderful job of explaining these principles. The book is meaty with insight and full of Biblical references to help the reader truly understand what it is to give all of our lives to God and why it’s so worthwhile to do.<br /><br />We all want to live life to the fullest, and by incorporating these principles into our daily walk, we are one step further along to that goal. Less of my ways and more of His.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18416085402278314676" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


