        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer199802018" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4417055823543295585">There’s a lot to love about Marja Verschoor-Meijers&apos; series inspired by the Ten Commandments. Instead of focusing on the don’ts (like &quot;do not steal&quot;), she encourages us to explore the flip side: what we’re exhorted to DO (in this case, give). It’s easy to see why this installment in her series is an award-winner. It hits us where we live, reminding us that there are more ways to steal than to swipe material things. And there are more ways to give than making financial donations. She helps us rep</span>
  <span id="freeText4417055823543295585" style="display:none">There’s a lot to love about Marja Verschoor-Meijers' series inspired by the Ten Commandments. Instead of focusing on the don’ts (like "do not steal"), she encourages us to explore the flip side: what we’re exhorted to DO (in this case, give). It’s easy to see why this installment in her series is an award-winner. It hits us where we live, reminding us that there are more ways to steal than to swipe material things. And there are more ways to give than making financial donations. She helps us replace miserly patterns with openhearted grace and challenges us about how to live biblically in the Spirit of the Law as truly cheerful givers. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4417055823543295585" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
