<span id="freeTextContainer15277252027429972371">This is a concise and well written book moving from the commandment of &quot;Thou Shalt not Steal&quot; to &quot;How can we be joyful givers&quot; and an exploration of how that move in attitude can enhance our lives. This is not deeply academic writing but is successful in its purpose which is to inspire us to review our own attitudes towards giving and our tendencies to want to hold on tightly to our money and possessions. </span>
  <span id="freeText15277252027429972371" style="display:none">This is a concise and well written book moving from the commandment of "Thou Shalt not Steal" to "How can we be joyful givers" and an exploration of how that move in attitude can enhance our lives. This is not deeply academic writing but is successful in its purpose which is to inspire us to review our own attitudes towards giving and our tendencies to want to hold on tightly to our money and possessions. </span>
